---
import Main from '../layouts/Main.astro';
---

<Main title="Educators" description="Teaching resources and curriculum guides for educators (coming soon).">

<style>
  .coming-soon {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 4rem auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .coming-soon h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--txt);
  }

  .coming-soon p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--txt2);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .features {
    background: var(--surf);
    border: 1px solid var(--bdr);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .features h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--txt);
  }

  .features ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .features li {
    padding: 0.8rem 0;
    color: var(--txt2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bdr);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.8rem;
  }

  .features li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .features li::before {
    content: "✓";
    color: var(--teal);
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .cta {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .cta a {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.9rem 2rem;
    background: var(--teal);
    color: var(--bg);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .cta a:hover {
    background: #5dd9bd;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .coming-soon {
      margin: 2rem auto;
      padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .coming-soon h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .features {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .features h2 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<div class="coming-soon">
  <h1>Educator Resources</h1>
  <p>We're building a comprehensive platform for educators to access teaching materials, lesson plans, and curriculum integration guides.</p>

  <div class="features">
    <h2>Coming Soon</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Ready-to-use lesson plans and teaching guides</li>
      <li>Curriculum integration resources for different education systems</li>
      <li>Downloadable worksheets and practice materials</li>
      <li>Assessment tools and evaluation frameworks</li>
      <li>Professional development content for educators</li>
      <li>Interactive tools for in-class use</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p>We're committed to supporting educators with free, high-quality resources to enhance student learning. If you're an educator interested in using Mathify.us resources in your classroom, we'd love to hear from you!</p>

  <div class="cta">
    <a href="mailto:hello@mathify.us">Get in Touch</a>
  </div>
</div>

</Main>
